HEADWORD: Haymow
<hw>Hay"mow`</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"mou`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A mow or mass of hay laid up in a barn for preservation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place in a barn where hay is
deposited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hayrack</ent>⟦br⟧
